        <div class="about-content">
          <h2 class="about-me">About Prof. Sandeep Chaudhary</h2>
          <p itemprop="description">
            Prof. Sandeep Chaudhary is the Dean of Administration and a
            <span class="highlight">Professor in the Department of Civil Engineering</span>
            at IIT Indore. With 27 years of professional experience, he has
            contributed as an academician, researcher, and industry expert in
            structural engineering and sustainable construction. His research
            focuses on the microstructural behavior of building materials,
            sustainable building products, and large-structure analysis. His work
            has resulted in
            <span class="highlight">two patents</span> and the first technology
            transfer at IIT Indore.
          </p>

          <p>
            He is part of an interdisciplinary team that secured an
            <span class="highlight">INR 100-crore grant</span> to establish a
            <span class="highlight">Technology Innovation Hub (TIH)</span>. His
            international collaborations include a recent invitation from the
            Government of the Russian Federation to develop a world-class research
            lab at NPI, Russia, leading a project on
            <span class="highlight">carbon-neutral technologies</span> for
            recycling industrial fuel waste into functional geopolymer materials.
          </p>

          <p>
            Prof. Chaudhary has been actively involved in prestigious national and
            international committees. He currently serves as the Secretary of the
            Technical Committee on
            <span class="highlight">"Life Cycle Maintenance of Concrete Infrastructures (TC-LCM)"</span>
            under the Asian Concrete Federation, contributing to advancements in
            concrete infrastructure sustainability.
          </p>
